  "prompt": "Why is my fridge not working but my freezer is?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why your refrigerator is not working while the freezer is still functioning:\n\n1. Faulty evaporator fan\n- The fan circulates cold air from the freezer to the fridge\n- If it's not working, the fridge won't cool properly\n\n2. Blocked air vent\n- The vent between freezer and fridge might be clogged with ice or debris\n- This prevents cold air from reaching the refrigerator section\n\n3. Defrost system issue\n- A malfunctioning defrost heater or timer can cause ice buildup\n- This can block airflow to the refrigerator\n\n4. Thermostat problems\n- The temperature control might be faulty\n- This can prevent the fridge from receiving proper cooling signals\n\n5. Compressor or condenser issues\n- Though less likely if the freezer is working, there could be partial compressor failure\n\n6. Damaged door seal\n- A bad seal can prevent proper cooling in the fridge section\n\nRecommended steps:\n- Check for obvious obstructions\n- Listen for fan and compressor sounds\n- Verify temperature settings\n- Consider calling a professional appliance repair technician for diagnosis",
